hy are you crying?â€&#10;&#10;Peter could be exceeding polite also, having learned the grand manner&#10;at fairy ceremonies, and he rose and bowed to her beautifully. She was&#10;much pleased, and bowed beautifully to him from the bed.&#10;&#10;â€œWhatâ€™s your name?â€ he asked.&#10;&#10;â€œWendy Moira Angela Darling,â€ she replied with some satisfaction. â€œWhat&#10;is your name?â€&#10;&#10;â€œPeter Pan.â€&#10;&#10;She was already sure that he must be Peter, but it did seem a&#10;comparatively short name.&#10;&#10;â€œIs that all?â€&#10;&#10;â€œYes,â€ he said rather sharply. He felt for the first time that it was a&#10;shortish name.&#10;&#10;â€œIâ€™m so sorry,â€ said Wendy Moira Angela.&#10;&#10;â€œIt doesnâ€™t matter,â€ Peter gulped.&#10;&#10;She asked where he lived.&#10;&#10;â€œSecond to the right,â€ said Peter, â€œand then straight on till morning.â€&#10;&#10;â€œWhat a funny address!â€&#10;&#10;Peter had a sinking. For the first time he felt that perhaps it was a&#10;funny address.&#10;&#10;â€œNo, it isnâ€™t,â€ he said.&#10;&#10;â€œI mean,â€ Wendy said nicely, remembering that she was hostess, â€œis that&#10;what they put on the letters?â€&#10;&#10;He wished she had not mentioned letters.&#10;&#10;â€œDonâ€™t get any letters,â€ he said contemptuously.&#10;&#10;â€œBut your mother gets letters?â€&#10;&#10;â€œDonâ€™t have a mother,â€ he said. Not only had he no mother, but he had&#10;not the slightest desire to have one. He thought them very over-rated&#10;persons. Wendy, however, felt at once that she was in the presence of a&#10;tragedy.&#10;&#10;â€œO Peter, no wonder you were crying,â€ she said, and got out of bed and&#10;ran to him.&#10;&#10;â€œI wasnâ€™t crying about mothers,â€ he said rather indignantly. â€œI was&#10;crying because I canâ€™t get my shadow to stick on. Besides, I wasnâ€™t&#10;crying.â€&#10;&#10;â€œIt has come off?â€&#10;&#10;â€œYes.â€&#10;&#10;Then Wendy saw the shadow on the floor, looking so draggled, and she&#10;was frightfully sorry for Pe